Key Match Events: Alperen Şengün shined with 26 points, 10 rebounds, six assists and two steals.
Jalen Green erupted for 22 of his game-high 29 points in a pivotal third quarter.
Amen Thompson added a monstrous 20 points and 15 rebounds.
Fred VanVleet dished out 19 points and 12 assists.
The Rockets posted 40 points in the third quarter, fueled by Green and Şengün’s combined brilliance, shooting 15 of 23.
Houston turned 18 Washington turnovers into 35 points, extending their lead to as much as 26.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Rockets, now boasting 24 wins, remain a dominant force in the Western Conference.
The Wizards, struggling at the bottom of the Eastern Conference with a 6-28 record, could not maintain their momentum.
The Wizards lost Kyle Kuzma to a calf injury in the first half, further stifling their chances.
